Author: SubBiscuit
Text: These are very common feelings with EDs. They often have aspects of "imposter syndrome".  People have died above UW with EDs and you can still do irreversible damage to your body (esp your bones).  If you arent ready for recovery then you arent but getting diagnosed made me feel a lot better and was the start to me looking into recovery.  You can always start the recovery process for just therapy and feeling better without aiming for weight gain. That might ease some worries about recovery.
